<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Mon, 6 Sep 2004 06:42:18 -0700 (PDT)
From: Marianne Hopp <mjhopp12@yahoo.com>
Source: WHO Outbreak News 6 Sep 2004 [edited]
<http://www.who.int/csr/don/2004_09_06/en/>

Hepatitis E in Chad - update 2
----------------
Between 26 Jun and 2 Sep 2004 a total of 1077 cases and 35 deaths
(case fatality rate 3.2 percent) of suspected hepatitis E has been
reported from the refugee camps Goz Amer (973 cases; 31 deaths) and
Goz Abal (63 cases; 3 deaths) and from the neighboring communities
(Koukou, Am-Ouchar, Am-Bitin, Habile, Aradibe).
The WHO investigation team arrived in Koukou near the Goz Amer camp
on Sat 2 Sep 2004. They will identify the risk factors of the
disease, and recommend appropriate control measures, including those
targeting water and sanitation.
For more information
Hepatitis E in Chad - update
<http://www.who.int/csr/don/2004_08_31/en/>
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[This is an increase of 118 cases and 5 deaths in the area since 20
Aug 2004 -- see 1st ref. below. The refugees are from Darfur, Sudan,
where there is also a hepatitis E epidemic. - Mod.JW]
